  "description": "A morphism class in the predicate category, induced by the diagonal collapse (s, o) ↦ (s, s) on the entity-pair index. Builds a binary predicate q whose value at (s, o) depends only on p's value at (s, s), broadcasting the subject-diagonal content across all object coordinates. One of the four canonical generators of the predicate category.",
